# Semgrep ignore — Pinakes
# See issue #146 for the full triage of the 117 findings from
# `semgrep scan --pro --config=auto` (all 0 real vulnerabilities).
# This file keeps future scans focused on NEW signal by excluding
# vendored/bundled/minified code and documentation placeholders.

# --- Third-party / vendored code (not ours to fix) ---
vendor/
node_modules/
public/assets/tinymce/
public/assets/uppy/
public/assets/sweetalert2/

# --- Minified bundles (false positives from minified output:
#     detect-non-literal-regexp on public/assets/661.bundle.js etc.) ---
*.min.js
*.min.css
public/assets/*.bundle.js

# --- Documentation with placeholder credentials ---
# `sk_live_…` example keys in plugin docs trip the stripe/picatic
# secret detectors (3+3 ERROR findings in #146) — they are illustrative,
# not real keys.
storage/plugins/api-book-scraper/README.md
storage/plugins/*/SERVER_IMPLEMENTATION_GUIDE.md

# --- Build-time tooling (no user input, runs only on `npm run build`) ---
